Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a sumptuous free kick from a position to the left of centre, making it 2-0 for England.
Jack Grealish opened the scoring with a cool finish after a lovely flick from Angel Gomes.
Declan Rice scored the third goal from a cross by Ollie Watkins.
Arttu Hoskonen scored a late consolation goal for Finland, heading home from a corner.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley needed this win to return to the tranquil progress of his first camp in September after the mayhem of the Wembley defeat against Greece.
The match was a return to a more conventional style for England, especially with Harry Kane back from injury to play as the number 9.
Jack Grealish has enjoyed playing under Lee Carsley, scoring in his third start under him.
